        <p>
          Use the design system to lay out the content on your serviceâ€™s pages
          vertically in a uniform and consisted manner.
        </p>
        <h2 id="component-margin" tabindex="-1">
          Component margin <a class="anchor-link" href="#component-margin"> </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
          The system uses margin bottom attribute on each component to manage
          vertical spacing and distinguishes
          <a href="../typography">typography</a> ( i.e.
          <code>&lt;p&gt;,&lt;ul&gt;,&lt;ol&gt; </code>),
          <a href="../typography/#headings">headings </a> (i.e.
          <code
            >&lt;h1&gt;,&lt;h2&gt;,&lt;h3&gt;,&lt;h4&gt;,&lt;h5&gt;,&lt;h6&gt;</code
          >) from the <a href="../../components">rest of the components</a>.
        </p>
        <p>The following margin bottom values must be applied:</p>
        <table class="govcy-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Component Type</th>
              <th>margin-bottom value</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>typography</td>
              <td>16px</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>headings</td>
              <td>24px</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>rest of components</td>
              <td>24px</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <h2 id="vertical-spacing-with-govcy-css" tabindex="-1">
          Vertical spacing with GOVCY CSS
          <a class="anchor-link" href="#vertical-spacing-with-govcy-css"> </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
          The grid system automatically adjusts vertical spacing when using
          the<a href="../../getting_started/#css-and-javascript"> govcy css</a>
          for typography, headings and components that include the
          <code>govcy-form-control</code> class.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you like to implement the same vertical spacing as decribed above,
          you can use the
          <a href="../../css_utilities/#margin%2C-padding"
            >margin utility classes</a
          >
          as follows
        </p>
        <table class="govcy-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Utility Class</th>
              <th>margin-bottom value</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>govcy-mb-3</td>
              <td>16px</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>govcy-mb-4</td>
              <td>24px</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>
